00028 /*
00029  * When the MPU is used the standard (non MPU) API functions are mapped to
00030  * equivalents that start "MPU_", the prototypes for which are defined in this
00031  * header files.  This will cause the application code to call the MPU_ version
00032  * which wraps the non-MPU version with privilege promoting then demoting code,
00033  * so the kernel code always runs will full privileges.
00034  */
00035 
00036 
